pr_body:
Introducing py3status popups.

What are these I hear you ask.  When the user clicks on a module we can now display a popup menu.
The popups are drawn using dzen2.

example:

```
my_module {
    on_click 1 = "popup hello"  # display some text fairly pointless
}

my_module {
    on_click 1 = "popup Firefox:exec firefox"   # launcher
}

my_module {
    on_click 1 = "popup Firefox:exec firefox\nChrome:exec google-chrome"  # 2 item launcher
}

my_module {
    on_click 1 = "popup Firefox:exec firefox\n"
    on_click 1 += "Chrome:exec google-chrome"  # 2 item launcher just written different
}

my_module {
    on_click 1 = "popup `calc`"  # run a command and output to the popup
}
```

There is also some functionality to allow modules to use popups eg in their on_click()

I need to do a few tidy ups and also write documentation etc but I though it would be good to post this here so people have a chance to make suggestions on how we can improve it etc.

I'll also improve how we choose the menu colors as currently hardcoded but we can get these from i3config or our config.

Feedback welcome as ever.

